-- German Family-Owned Firms Doubt Euro, Merkel, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-06-14T06:26:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/german-family-owned-firms-doubt-euro-merkel-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany’s  Foundation for Family
Business  said a growing number of entrepreneurs doubt that the
euro will endure as a currency, Handelsblatt reported, citing
Brun-Hagen Hennerkes, the foundation’s executive board chairman.  Support for German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s goal of
fiscal discipline is diminishing among the leaders of European
countries, the Dusseldorf-based newspaper cited Hennerkes, who
represents about 350 family-owned companies, as saying in an
interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
